<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>About Brian Siano</TITLE>
<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:lippard@skeptic.com">
</HEAD>
<BODY>
Brian Siano is a Senior Editor of <EM>The Humanist Magazine</EM> and a freelance
writer.  His regular column, "The Skeptical Eye," deals with pseudoscience
and fringe-culture:  topics have included UFO conspiracy theories,
comic-book censorship, Satanic cult accounts, and violence-and-the-media
claims.  He has a B.A. in English from Temple University.  Current cultural
influences include Stanley Kubrick's films, Harlan Ellison's short
stories, Christopher Hitchens' essays, comic books, <EM>Mystery Science
Theater 3000</EM>, Jelly Roll Morton's "Dead Man Blues" and reggae music.
He's thirty-one, single, and has too much free time.  He can be reached
by Email at <A HREF = "mailto:revpk@cellar.org">revpk@cellar.org</A>.
</BODY>
</HTML>
