<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>About Brian Siano</TITLE>
<LINK REV = "made" HREF = "mailto:lippard@skeptic.com">
</HEAD>
<BODY>
Brian Siano is a regular contributor to <EM>Skeptic</EM> magazine,
a long-time observer of the skeptical movement, and a former Senior
Editor of <EM>The Humanist</EM> and a freelance writer.  His
regular column, "The Skeptical Eye," dealt with pseudoscience and
fringe-culture; topics have included UFO conspiracy theories,
comic-book censorship, Satanic cult accounts, and violence-and-the-media
claims.  He has a B.A. in English from Temple University.  Current
cultural influences include Stanley Kubrick's films, Harlan Ellison's
short stories, Christopher Hitchens' essays, comic books, <EM>Mystery
Science Theater 3000</EM>, Jelly Roll Morton's "Dead Man Blues"
and reggae music.  He can be reached by email at <A HREF = "mailto:siano@cceb.med.upenn.edu">siano@cceb.med.upenn.edu</A>.
