bites, there is no doubt survival advantage to the FIV virus, as with 
rabies, in making infected cats unusually aggressive. Perhaps this 
brain-modifying protein once served a similar purpose in lower primates 
as in cats, changing behavior in subtle ways to encourage lentivirus 
spread. 
