<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>About Bradley Lepper</TITLE>
<LINK REV = "made" HREF = "mailto:lippard@skeptic.com">
</HEAD>
<BODY>
Dr. Bradley Lepper is Curator of Archaeology at the Ohio Historical
Society and an occasional visiting Assistant Professor in the
Department of Sociology and Anthropology at Denison University
in Granville, Ohio.  He is the editor of the journal <EM>Current
Research in the Pleistocene</EM>, and has contributed numerous
articles to various books and journals on the Ice Age peoples
of midcontinental North America.  More recently, Lepper has been
studying the later peoples of the Ohio Valley who constructed the
magnificent mounds and earthworks for which this region is
renowned.  Lepper's research has been featured in popular magazines
such as <EM>Archaeology</EM>, <EM>Discover</EM>, and <EM>National
Geographic</EM>.
</BODY>
