In Reply to: <a href="761.html">Re: Full Skeptics??</a> posted by Stephen Charchuk on January 02, 1997 at 16:46:16:<p>
: : I am certainly open to evidence...As far as I know I can not know and <br>: : therefore believe (or not believe) in anything...I certainly would<br>: : welcome any proof of anything.  I am totally open to new ideas/theories<br>: : because I have no believes of my own to close my mind.<p>: You wouldn't be human if you didn't have at least somes beliefs. Do you believe that the Earth is a sphere, do you believe in the laws of physics?<p>Who told you I was human...I came in on a UFO from a far away plant...<br>I don't have believes, not in anything...although just to function<br>here (as opposed to my home planet) one has to assume certain things<br>will happen (throw a ball up and it comes down) however I don't believe<br>this is nessasarily the way the universe works or even the world; thats<br>just how it seems right now.<p>
