      <h1>Re: Full Skeptics??</h1>
    </center>
<hr size=7 width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="#followups">Follow Ups</a> ] [ <a href="#postfp">Post Followup</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/skepticboard.html">Skeptics Society Message Board</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/faq.html">FAQ</a> ]</center>
<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by David on January 03, 1997 at 09:24:54:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="769.html">Re: Full Skeptics??</a> posted by grasshopper on January 02, 1997 at 20:42:34:<p>
: : : I am certainly open to evidence...As far as I know I can not know and <br>: : : therefore believe (or not believe) in anything...I certainly would<br>: : : welcome any proof of anything.  I am totally open to new ideas/theories<br>: : : because I have no believes of my own to close my mind.<p>: : You wouldn't be human if you didn't have at least somes beliefs. Do you believe that the Earth is a sphere, do you believe in the laws of physics?<p>: Who told you I was human...I came in on a UFO from a far away plant...<br>: I don't have believes, not in anything...although just to function<br>: here (as opposed to my home planet) one has to assume certain things<br>: will happen (throw a ball up and it comes down) however I don't believe<br>: this is nessasarily the way the universe works or even the world; thats<br>: just how it seems right now.<p>Don't you believe Descartes' Cogito: "I think, therefore I am".  If you believe that, and I think it is pretty hard not to, you can start to build on that for other beliefs.
<br>
