Name: <input type=text name="name" size=50><br>
E-Mail: <input type=text name="email" size=50><p>
Subject: <input type=text name="subject"value="Re: Full Skeptics??" size=50><p>
Comments:<br>
<textarea name="body" COLS=70 ROWS=20>
: : 
: : : What if our minds our computer programs-preset, every thought was
: : : programmed...by who for what purpose....?-explains nothing to me.

: : I've got news for you, our brains are computers, organic computers.
: : Our minds are a group of self-programming metaprograms. We use many pre-programmed responses called instincts, which are encoded in our RNA.

: I'm not talking about that...I'm saying I may not have any self-determination.

</textarea>
