Posted by <a href="mailto:nosferat@auracom.com">Stephen Charchuk</a> on January 03, 1997 at 23:13:37:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="802.html">Re: Full Skeptics??</a> posted by grasshopper on January 03, 1997 at 21:29:05:<p>
: I puppet can ask questions, or rather it could seem to ask questions.  I've<br>: created some good computer programs, maybe my thoughts are nothing more<br>: than a program...every thought is nothing more than a program...so I could<br>: say 'I think' but that is just part of the program....?<p>Of course it is part of a program. Our brains operate almost in the same way as computers do, with many interconnected nets and nodes and sub-programs. We are self-programming. <br>
