      <h1>Re: Full Skeptics??</h1>
    </center>
<hr size=7 width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="#followups">Follow Ups</a> ] [ <a href="#postfp">Post Followup</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/skepticboard.html">Skeptics Society Message Board</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/faq.html">FAQ</a> ]</center>
<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by grasshopper on January 04, 1997 at 09:23:16:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="809.html">Re: Full Skeptics??</a> posted by Stephen Charchuk on January 03, 1997 at 23:13:37:<p>
: : I puppet can ask questions, or rather it could seem to ask questions.  I've<br>: : created some good computer programs, maybe my thoughts are nothing more<br>: : than a program...every thought is nothing more than a program...so I could<br>: : say 'I think' but that is just part of the program....?<p>: Of course it is part of a program. Our brains operate almost in the same way as computers do, with many interconnected nets and nodes and sub-programs. We are self-programming. <p>I'm not talking self-programming...I'm saying I may be a machine, nothing<br>more there is no self no self-determination...I do not think I am merely<br>a preset programmed device-nothing more.
<br>
<br><hr size=7 width=75%><p>
