<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by <a href="mailto:nosferat@auracom.com">Stephen Charchuk</a> on January 01, 1997 at 22:44:49:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="705.html">Full Skeptics??</a> posted by Grasshopper on January 01, 1997 at 20:40:05:<p>
<br>: I'm new to this page so I haven't read all these posts; I don't<br>: really know where people stand so I'll just throw out what I think.<br>: I am a full skeptic I do not believe in anything, not people, not history, <br>: not science-nothing, because I can think of alternatives, so I can't know<br>: anything about the nature of the universe or the world.<br>: I see a lot of skeptics not believe in some things, but then believe in<br>: other things?!-respectfully grasshopper<p>It is important to have an open mind, but not so open that one's brains fall out. On the adverse a mind that is so closed that it would make a clam jealous is not way to look at the world either.<br>
<br>
