I don't believe in anything...Certainly there are some things that I <br>do to live in this world-I breath thinking it will be oxygen because<br>it is nessasary to live in this world, but if it was oxygen I won't be<br>suprised.  I say this is the way the world seems to work, so I live<br>accordingly so I function, however if I truly expected the world to behave<br>constantly I would be closed minded, so I am open to anything happening<br>because anything is probable.<br>I completely respect your ability to change and adapt and I too am that<br>way.  What you said is absolutely true; and I think all of us have become<br>frustrated with people that refuse to hear arguement.<br>When you say 'why not believe...' I say 'why believe'; Either way <br>probably doesn't matter as long as both stay completely open minded.<br>I like living this way because I feel centered and peaceful; you<br>probably feel the same about how you live.  I don't see flaw in either<br>of our arguements as long as open mindedness is present.<p>
