<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by Lynn on January 06, 1997 at 09:58:01:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="873.html">Christian values and morals?</a> posted by Stephen Charchuk on January 05, 1997 at 19:19:40:<p>
<br>: I've been hearing all over the news when ever some Republican or Evangelist comes on they keep talking about Christian family values and morals. Are these things any different than those for everyone else, or are Christians trying to claim that only they can have any of these values and morals in a positive way and that everyone else is automatically immoral and have no real values?<p><br>Hello Stephen,<p>There are those who are "a law unto themselves".  God esteems those who do what's right over those who claim to love Him and practice what is wrong.
<br>
