  <head>
    <title>Re: Christian values and morals?</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <center>
      <h1>Re: Christian values and morals?</h1>
    </center>
<hr size=7 width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="#followups">Follow Ups</a> ] [ <a href="#postfp">Post Followup</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/skepticboard.html">Skeptics Society Message Board</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/faq.html">FAQ</a> ]</center>
<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by Lynn on January 07, 1997 at 15:13:13:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="935.html">Re: Christian values and morals?</a> posted by Stephen Charchuk on January 07, 1997 at 12:43:25:<p>
<br>: : Could you please specify the "things" they want to enforce on everyone?  I am fairly familiar with their work, but was unaware of any desire to change our form of government.  <p>: <br>: School prayer for one. Their limited definition of what a family is, taking away a woman's right to chose what she can do with her body,<br>: make homosexuality illegal, etc, etc....<p>: : I'm not sure how this relates to what I was saying.  Perhaps were are talking about two different subjects. <p>: <br>: It relates in that they want to impose their limited view of the world on all.<p><br>Personally, I can't imagine why they would want school prayer.  If it was instituted, it would be so benign as to be worthless, or worse, contradictory to Christian teaching.  We can teach our children to pray at home.<br>As far as homosexuality is concerned, as long as it's not in my face, I think people have a perfect right to choose their own lifestyle. <br>I think the CC feels the same.  They just want to be sure that other peoples values are not imposed on us and our children.
<br>
<br><hr size=7 width=75%><p>
