: Good question.

: I looked up fundamentalism in Webster's and it is defined as &quot;the belief that all statements made in the Bible are literally true.&quot; and, &quot;a movement among Protestants holding that such belief is essential to Christian faith&quot;.  

: I believe that the Bible is inerrant, but I don't feel that the every part is meant to be taken in the literal sense.  Some of it is poetic, some is prophetic and uses a lot of symbols and metaphors, and some is quite literal.  I feel that one must believe the books have been passed from generation to generation without error in order to have trust in God's word as a roadmap for life.  I don't know if this makes me a fundamentalist or not.

