<br><hr size=7 width=75%><p>
<a name="postfp">Post a Followup</a><p>
<form method=POST action="http://www.skeptic.com/cgi-local/skepticboard.pl">
<input type=hidden name="followup" value="447">
<input type=hidden name="origname" value="Clay S">
<input type=hidden name="origemail" value="emptiness@aol.com">
<input type=hidden name="origsubject" value="The Problem of Fundamentalism in the World's Major Religions Today ">
<input type=hidden name="origdate" value="December 05, 1996 at 07:53:21">
Name: <input type=text name="name" size=50><br>
E-Mail: <input type=text name="email" size=50><p>
Subject: <input type=text name="subject" value="Re: The Problem of Fundamentalism in the World's Major Religions Today " size=50><p>
Comments:<br>
<textarea name="body" COLS=70 ROWS=20>
: THE PROBLEM OF FUNDAMENTALISM IN THE WORLDS MAJOR RELIGIONS TODAY 

: Today I had an encounter with a Christian Fundamentalist while waiting on a student of mine in a school 
: cafeteria.  I should have known that something was a little strange about this fellow from the &quot;blissed out&quot; 
: look he gave the heavens as he said a prayer before his meal.  Afterwards, he asked me what I did for a 
: living.  I told him that I teach Philosophy and Mathematics at a particular university in the USA.  This was 
: sufficient to open the floodgates of Fundamentalist Proselytizing Zeal.  He asked me where I was going 
: when I died.  My response was that the question makes little sense and that when human beings die, their 
: consciousness is extinguished like a fire when water is poured over it.  He told me that it is our relationship 
: with Jesus Christ that is all-important.  Depending upon this crucial association, he said, our Eternal Destiny 
: in Heaven or Hell is settled.  When I told him that I left religion up to those who were interested in it and 
: had little interest eschatological issues of this sort myself, he felt compelled to quote scripture to the effect 
: that &quot;It is appointed unto every man to live once&quot; and that  &quot;We will all stand before the Throne of 
: Judgment and be judged according to our relationship with Jesus.&quot;  I told him that these views were little 
: more than anthropomorphic and childish superstitions. He did not understand the word 
: &quot;anthropomorphism&quot; and was unclear as to the definition of &quot;superstition&quot; as well.  When  he asked me 
: what a &quot;superstition&quot; was  I told him that it is a belief compounded of legend, myth and wishful thinking 
: and hence, one which will not withstand logical, empirical, scientific and philosophical scrutiny.  This had 
: little impact, and he proceeded to talk of Heaven again.  I told him that I am enormously unimpressed with 
: talk about Heaven especially when such talk seems to utilize religious imagery and religious ideas right out 
: of Hollywood movies and comic books.  Rudolph Otto (&quot;The Idea of the Holy&quot;) and Mircea Eliade (&quot;The 
: Sacred and the Profane&quot;) and Pierre Hadot (&quot;Philosophy as a Way of Life&quot; and &quot;Plotinus or the Simplicity 
: of Vision&quot;) this isnt!! Moreover, when asked where Heaven is located, he seemed at a loss for an answer.  
: Even if he had said that Heaven is really another &quot;plane of existence, this would have made little 
: difference.  This is so since no one has been able to give any intelligible content to another plane of being 
: in the first place.

: Friends, the Fundamentalist Mentality worldwide is a fixed mindset characterized by diverse doctrine, but 
: with an immutable underlying structure.  Fundamentalism is little more than a sustained  ARGUMENTUM 
: AD BACULUM - the classic appeal to force.  The underlying structure of this Mindset is that unless one 
: affirms view X, then God, or the Cosmos, or whatever will see to it that you ETERNALLY PAY for 
: failure to do so.  Let us review some of the classic ad Baculum arguments in the worlds religions and 
: philosophies today:

: -If you fail to be a Marxist and affirm the socialist and communist doctrines, then the inexorable sweep and 
: tide of history toward the Classless Society will relegate you, forever, into insignificance.  Moreover, the 
: Revolution Itself may take your physical life as well!

: -Arminian Christians:  Unless you freely choose Gods great gift of Jesus Christ, then you will be damned to 
: Hell forever

: -Calvinistic Christians:  Your eternal salvation or damnation has already been DECREED, to His infinite 
: Glory, by God in The Inscrutable Counsels of Eternity before the very creation of the world.  He does only 
: and precisely THAT which PLEASES Him.  If you are unwilling to be Damned for his Sparkling Glory, 
: then you are surely among the reprobate and unelect.

: -Mahayana Buddhist Fundamentalists:  Unless the Mahayana Buddhist Views concerning Inherent 
: Existence (as taught by the Omniscient Nagarjuna), along with those regarding  Compassion and Nirvana, 
: are affirmed, one is advocating a philosophical and religious outlook characterized by either Over Negation 
: on the one hand,  or Under Negation on the other.  Moreover, if one fails to take the Bodhisattva Vows, 
: then one is relegated to an inferior Nirvana Forever.  

: -New Age Fundamentalists:  Unless you affirm that Spiritually involves Following  your Bliss to Infinite 
: and Eternal Ecstasy along with the Omniscience and Perfection of both our Guru and our Timeless Yogic 
: Paths,  then your are mired in delusion, hubris and Spiritual Ignorance.

: Please see that the Fundamentalist Mindset is not only inimical to personal and social harmony, but it is, 
: furthermore, merely a thinly veiled THREAT at best.  Not only this, but Fundamentalism is really nothing 
: more than a &quot;fill in the blank&quot; mindset.  Thus the doctrines differ, but the obscurantism, intolerance and 
: implicit violence remain the immutable structural features of this phenomenon.

: In closing, let me take this opportunity to invite all to construct ADEQUATE religious and philosophical 
: visions of the world that will withstand the most rigorous moral, axiological, logical, philosophical, 
: scientific and Authentically Contemplative scrutiny we can bring to bear upon them.

: Clay S.

</textarea>
