In Reply to: <a href="391.html">What would a rationalist society look like?</a> posted by Karen on November 28, 1996 at 21:36:35:<p>
 <br>: I'm curious to know what a society run by atheists <br>would look like? <br>: What holidays would you celebrate?  Would you have <br>charities?  Whom would they serve? <br>: What would happen to religious art or church <br>buildings?  How would you avoid becoming as <br>: brutal as Nazi Germany or the Soviet Union?  I <br>don't know of anywhere else I can ask these <br>: questions and get a reasonable answer, and I don't <br>see that anyone has examined this much.  <br> <br>Why do you fear that a rationalist society would be <br>brutal and devoid of beauty, tradition & <br>compassion?Many religions seek to control behavior <br>through fear & guilt.  A rationalist acts based on <br>clearly thought out moral framework.  I do not need <br>to identify with a diety to appreciate nature, art, <br>or music; nor do I need be a Christian to happily <br>participate in nthe spirit of generosity and family <br>tradition that surround xmas.  Many holiday <br>traditions such as xmas trees and easter eggs are of <br>pagan origin.  The values of cooperation, <br>respect,fairness and honesty are not limited to those <br>with religious beliefs.  As for church buildings - <br>maybe the billions spent on building, furnishing, and <br>maintaining them could be better spent (for instance <br>on education or health).
