Posted by Amanda on December 31, 1996 at 02:00:37:<p>
Everyone will check this out no doubt!   Here's another discovery I don't understand. The cellular attraction which brings together the egg-cell and sperm is due to a chemical action allied to smell or taste!? What does that mean allied to smell or taste? All of these subjects I've been posting are written about briefly in a book I'm reading that isn't really scientific so instead of doing the time-consuming, exhausting research of the various ideas I thought I'd follow that path of least resistance and see if anyone here knew anything about it. The book was published in 1969 so I imagine there have been quite a few advances made in such areas - each new day, I find I'm falling further and further behind! This particular concept is also called "cellular affinity" or "sexual cell-love" - it certainly confirms my theory that scientists are the wittiest people around. 
<br>
