Posted by Lynn on December 15, 1996 at 18:02:04:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="516.html">Validating scientific discovery-some answers.  </a> posted by Charles Pique on December 15, 1996 at 00:13:49:<p>
: <br>: : <br>: : : : Dear Peter,<br>: : : :      I feel you have missed my entire point.  When put it into the simplest terms, it comes down to this...You either believe that the universe has it's own intelligence and created itself, all this happened by accident, or that there is a God who created this universe.  It takes faith to believe whichever theory you choose, since no one can prove that his set of beliefs is the right one.  I choose the latter of the three possibilities.  Can you prove me wrong?<p>: : : I can't prove you wrong but as someone posted in an earlier note if you say <br>: : : God created the universe you open yourself to the question "Who created<br>: : : God?"  And don't try to tell me that "God is" or you have to accept people<br>: : : who say "The universe is".  As you rightly point out, you have to have a<br>: : : set of beliefs whatever you believe, its just that for me there is far<br>: : : more evidence to support a big bang than a God and again, to me, it is far<br>: : : more likely that matter is created from nothing than an all-powerful,<br>: : : omniscient super-being.<p>: : <br>: : You have every right to your opinion.  Thanks for acknowledging my point.<p>: : Lynn<p>: I might be late in this discussion but some experiments you might not<br>: be aware of - Pulling particles out of the vacuum a nuclear experiment.<br>: Virtual particles in quantum electromagnetic theory have been <br>: confirmed.<br>: The Big Bang theory calls for a universe that created itself. This is no<br>: big stunt anymore since self creation can be whitnessed in many labs.<br>: Apparently the initial point was nothing. Some time later and therafter<br>: the positive rest mass plus kinetic energy was canceled by the <br>: negative gravitational potential energy so today it still adds up to<br>: nothing. Information like writing on ice can be easily erased and that<br>: is what our planet is made of.<br>: For a more rigorous treatment write me at pk3.14@juno.com.<br>: Charles <p>Dear Charles,<p>You're talkin' way over my head.  Can you put your argument in laymen's terms?
