<textarea name="body" COLS=70 ROWS=20>
: : Does anyone know much about Tai Chi? I've heard some claims that
: : Tai Chi masters have paranormal abilities. For example, one claim
: : is that a Tai Chi master can immobilize an attacker simply by pointing
: : at him. Naturally, I'm skeptical of these claims.

: : I guess if Tai Chi masters did have extraordinary abilities, it may
: : not necessarily be a supernatural or spiritual phenomenon. It may be
: : some physical effect that we have yet to understand scientifically.
: : - Jason

: 
: Having wasted a few years now, on and off, on tai chi, I can offer you
: my opinion.  Tai Chi is a good exercise for elderly people who are
: starting to loose their balance.  It teaches body awareness, and may
: prevent someone from falling and breaking a hip.  There is no aerobic
: benefit.

: As far as developing paranormal abilities, the martial arts is filled
: with self-delusion.  People trying to transform thenselves into 
: supermen.  I have seen a kung fu &quot;master&quot; get seriously stomped in
: a bar fight with a larger person.  If this stuff was possible to any
: degree, law enforcement and military people would have figured it 
: out by now.

: So save yourself the time, unless you are someone who has trouble
: unwinding.  If, like me, you are trying to &quot;cultivate a vigorous 
: spirit&quot;, stay well away from it.

</textarea>
