Posted by grasshopper on January 04, 1997 at 09:39:42:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="812.html">Tai Chi</a> posted by Jason on January 04, 1997 at 00:49:52:<p>
: Does anyone know much about Tai Chi? I've heard some claims that<br>: Tai Chi masters have paranormal abilities. For example, one claim<br>: is that a Tai Chi master can immobilize an attacker simply by pointing<br>: at him. Naturally, I'm skeptical of these claims.<p>: I guess if Tai Chi masters did have extraordinary abilities, it may<br>: not necessarily be a supernatural or spiritual phenomenon. It may be<br>: some physical effect that we have yet to understand scientifically.<br>: - Jason<p>I do martial arts, not tai chi (but they all have the same roots)...<br>many of these 'magical things' can be explained by science (psycology mostly)...<br>These masters use there bodies more effectively than we can image...I have<br>heard stories of things extremely extremely mystical, but I doubt the masters<br>would explain this as more than practice and mastery of the body and mind.
