<textarea name="body" COLS=70 ROWS=20>
: : Does anyone have any theses as to why Skeptical books
: : are so hard to find, especially compared to the thousands
: : of true-believer ones?

: I think it is relatively easy to understand why there is a plethora of true-believers books and a dearth of skeptical books. Consider that believer-books typically tell people that there is an infinitely powerful creator that has a personal interest in you and that you will not die but be incredibly happy with Him for all eternity. We skeptics tell them that this is it and there probably is no such wonderful being and the idea you will be exstatically happy with Her for all eternity is simply a myth. Which message has sales appeal?

</textarea>
