<html>
  <head>
    <title>Re: Unlikely Existence of God</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <center>
      <h1>Re: Unlikely Existence of God</h1>
    </center>
<hr size=7 width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="#followups">Follow Ups</a> ] [ <a href="#postfp">Post Followup</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/skepticboard.html">Skeptics Society Message Board</a> ] [ <a href="http://www.skeptic.com/skepticboard/faq.html">FAQ</a> ]</center>
<hr size=7 width=75%><p>
Posted by <a href="mailto:lgrant@netonecom.net">Lynn</a> on December 28, 1996 at 16:11:33:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="609.html">Re: Unlikely Existence of God</a> posted by Stephen Charchuk on December 28, 1996 at 11:53:42:<p>
: : Obviously I disagree with you.  I could take every argument you make and turn it around to prove my own point, but I doubt if I could convince you.  There is only one way to know for sure if God is real.  <br>: First you would have to accept the possibility that there is a God.  Then you would have to open you mind and heart and sincerely humble yourself before Him and just say "God, if you are there would you please reveal yourself to me?"  You'd have to have the right attitude and little persistence, but I guarantee if you "keep knocking the door will be opened".  I suspect that most people at this site would find that to be a very hard thing to do, since, even if there is a God, he has already been judged to be cruel, uncaring, judgemental,...pick your own adjective.  <p>: There is no truly objective way to prove or disprove the existence of a god while one is alive, you can accept and believe all you want, but that isn't proof. The only way that it could be proven either way is to die. <p>: The evidence for this "judgement" is his/hers/its believers' own writings.<p><br>It cannot be proven to the world, but it can be proven in the heart of the individual.  Once you die, it's too late Stephen. 
<br>
<br><hr size=7 width=75%><p>
